**1\. Introduction**

**1.1 Purpose**

This Software Design Document (SDD) is intended to provide a detailed description of the Circular Dichroism Spectrometer (CD Spec) application via the use of visual diagrams and models. This SDD will describe the CD Spec application through these provided diagrams and will detail the architecture and design of the application. All aspects of the application will be defined visually, including the design of the application’s data, interfaces, as well as its overall architectural design. This document's primary function is to provide the viewer with an understanding of the CD Spec application’s structuring, both internal and external, as well as to be a useful tool for all parties involved in the development of this application, including the client and developers, as well as future users of the software.

Designs included within this SDD are as follows:

1. **Data Design:** the application’s data design shall provide an understanding of the application’s data and how it will be stored and/or used. The data design will also include data flow diagrams that illustrate how the data will be processed within the CD Spec application.  
2. **Architecture Design:** the architecture design will illustrate the overall structure of the CD Spec application, and all its components and functionalities, as well as their relationships within the system. This element of the application acts as the blueprints of the overall application, illustrating what the application will look like when developed.  
3. **Interface Design:** the interface design will illustrate the CD Spec application’s appearance and how it will be viewed from the user’s perspective. Here, the design of the software’s screen is drawn (roughly) for the viewer’s understanding. Also known as the presentation layer, this design element will also present all internal or external interfaces within the application.  
4. **Procedural Design:** the procedural design shall detail the internal logic that will make up the CD Spec application. This design illustrates how the program will function on the programming level, and will be explained via the usage of either visual imagery or pseudo code.

**1.5 System Overview**

The Circular Dichroism Spectrometer (CD Spec Spec) software shall be a functional database housed within a constructed web application. This software shall be utilized by both instructors and students to monitor spectral changes in structure between protein-DNA interactions. Users of this web application shall be able to create three forms of accounts. These accounts include a public user account, a student user account, and an administrator account. Each account type shall have specific abilities and/or limitations imposed. A public user may only view submitted protein-DNA data, they may not edit the data in any way or submit data themselves. A student user may view and submit protein-DNA data, they may not edit the data in any way. An administrator has full functionality, meaning that they may view, submit, and edit all data within the database. 

This CD Spec software shall perform calculations within the backend in order to monitor changes and differences between the data within the database.
